OL,7,FFollowing the investigation, Ms
OL,8,FHermosilla said she believes her
OL,9,Femployer did not communicate clearly
OL,10,Fwith her about either the outcome of
OL,11,Fthe investigation or the disciplinary
OL,12,Faction taken.
OL,14,FShe believed that the colleague would
OL,15,Fnot be returning to work. She was then
OL,16,Fadvised that they would be returning
OL,17,Fto their role. Ms Hermosilla has found
OL,18,Fthe whole process and its outcome very
OL,19,Fupsetting and distressing.
